Selecting Product Debit allows the user to select between Billing and Operating account as the charge account type. In this flow, billing account
is selected as the charge account type.
The success alert banner informs the user that the Billing Preferences have been successfully updated. The Billing updates are reflected within
the Company - Billing card and the Service Billing Preferences card.

Once services are set up, billing must be set up for each of the services. Two services have been added, account activity and wire payment
tracker, so there are two cards representative of these services. Since Billing account was selected as the charge account type, there is the
ability to add two accounts to bill for each service, one CAD account and one USD account. At least one of the two account fields must be filled,
as both are not necessary to be filled in order to continue with the flow.
There is also an option to provide supporting information up to 25mb per file with acceptable file formats being .xlxs, .csv, .txt, .doc, and .pdf. The
Supporting Information card is still a work in progress.
